#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/polynomial/laguerre.py:docstring
#: of numpy.polynomial.laguerre.lagint:66
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/polynomial/laguerre.py:docstring
#: of numpy.polynomial.laguerre.lagint:67
msgid ""
"Note that the result of each integration is *multiplied* by `scl`. Why is "
"this important to note?  Say one is making a linear change of variable :math:"
"`u = ax + b` in an integral relative to `x`.  Then :math:`dx = du/a`, so one "
"will need to set `scl` equal to :math:`1/a` - perhaps not what one would "
"have first thought."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/polynomial/laguerre.py:docstring
#: of numpy.polynomial.laguerre.lagint:73
msgid ""
"Also note that, in general, the result of integrating a C-series needs to be "
"\"reprojected\" onto the C-series basis set.  Thus, typically, the result of "
"this function is \"unintuitive,\" albeit correct; see Examples section below."
msgstr ""

